What occurs in derivatives: Observing the Open Interest, a significant increase coincides with a rise in price. For example, after a price rise, the Open Interest rose from 7.9 billion to 9.7 billion, representing a total increase of 1.8 billion. The majority of this increase was concentrated in long positions, starting from a price of 28,400.The Open Interest subsequently entered a range of moderate variation, which reduced the actual disposal probability from 9.7 billion to 8.8 billion, resulting from liquidations and profit gains.
